== Historical Background == The shrine was originally established during the Chōhō 3rd year (1001) by Numaha Giemon no Jo Sadakatsu after driving out bandits who had been threatening travelers in the "Difficult Forest" (Nangi Mori). Initially located in Kurikiba, it was relocated multiple times due to fires and reconstruction efforts. The deity was later identified as {{ill|Ama-no-Iwato no Kami|ja|天石門別神|1=Ama-no-Iwato no Kami}}, and the shrine underwent significant rebuilding in the Shōwa era.
== Subsidiary Shrines == * Wakamiya Hachiman (deity: {{ill|Emperor Nintoku|ja|仲徳天皇}}) * Suijin Shrine (deity: {{ill|Mizuhanome|ja|蔓象女神}}) * Mikuwasha Shrine (deity: {{ill|Toyouke|ja|豐受女神}})
== Accessibility == * Accessible via bus stops on the local Mie-Kinki bus line.
